The bug is in the second loop. This loop has a for-each-loop. The for-each-loop goes over a collection (i.e., the list) but the list itself is not updated. The bug occurs because the list is not updated. The updated list can only be accessed in the loop. Hence, the list itself can only be accessed in the for-each-loop. 

##### The bug is:
```java
