In the shortest_paths method, the weight_by_node map has a size of 16. In the first for-each loop, the size of the map is still 16. In the second for-each loop, the size of the map is now 2. This means that the for-each loop is over the keys of the map. However, in the second for-each loop, the map is updated. Hence, the first for-each loop is no longer over the keys of the map. The second for-each loop now goes over the values of the map.

